==Definition==
'''Autotelism''' is the belief that an entity or event has within itself its own meaning or purpose.  In literature or art, a it is the belief that a work, having been created, is a justification in and of itself.  Autotelic poems usually use a unified rhetorical device to frame the poem in a singular idea. 
